references.paper_title: Cryptanalytic Extraction of Neural Network Models
references.reason: This paper is the foundational work for the cryptanalytic model extraction methods discussed and improved upon in the current research.

references.paper_title: Polynomial Time Cryptanalytic Extraction of Neural Network Models
references.reason: This paper introduces significant improvements to the original cryptanalytic method, particularly regarding the efficiency of sign extraction, which is a crucial aspect of the overall approach.

references.paper_title: High Accuracy and High Fidelity Extraction of Neural Networks
references.reason: This work provides a comprehensive categorization of model extraction strategies and offers valuable context for understanding the broader landscape of attacks against machine learning models.
This paper delves into the challenges and techniques associated with reverse-engineering deep neural networks, providing useful background information on the complexities of this type of attack.
This paper explores the feasibility of extracting model parameters from deep neural networks using cryptanalytic methods, offering valuable insights into the practical aspects of this technique.
